USER:
Produce descriptions for a Hugr module using input json, consider data-source context if provided.

[INPUT JSON]
{
  "name": "{{ .Name }}",
  "description": "{{ .Description }}",
  "tables": {{ .TablesJSON }},
  "views": {{ .ViewsJSON }},
  "functions": {{ .FunctionsJSON }},
  "mutation_functions": {{ .MutationFunctionsJSON }},
  "submodules": {{ .SubmodulesJSON }},
  "data_source_context": {{ .DataSourceContextsJSON }},
}

[TASK]
Return ONE JSON with the exact shape below (English only; no extra keys):

{
  "short": "1–2 sentences: what this module contains and key tables/views/functions; mention module/source to avoid vacuum context",
  "long":  "≈400 tokens: business meaning & typical use; key arguments and why;
            key tables/views/functions and their significance; consider data-source context",
  "query_type": "1–2 sentences: describe the GraphQL query type for this module, if module has tables or views.",
  "mutation_type": "1–2 sentences: describe the GraphQL mutation type for this module, if module has tables.",
  "function_type": "1–2 sentences: describe the GraphQL function root type for this module, if module has functions.",
  "mutation_function_type": "1–2 sentences: describe the GraphQL mutation function root type for this module, if module has mutation functions.",
}

Constraints:
- Do NOT invent fields, relations or capabilities not present in the input.
- Do not use in descriptions the table, views and function names, instead use their business meaning.
- Do not use the module name in the short and long description, instead use their business meaning.
- Keep “short” succinct; keep “long” around 400 tokens; keep blurbs within the given limits.
- If the module name is empty (""), assume it's the root module - GraphQL schema, Describe the overall purpose and functionality of the schema.